<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="528" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[131,775,617,799]" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">
DISTRIBUTION. — Zagros Mountains (Kurdistan, Ilam, Lorestan, Fars, West of Esfahan, East of Khuzestan, Hormozgan, and West of Kerman Provinces (
<bibRefCitation author="MORSHED S. &amp; PATTON J. L." box="[325,569,670,694]" pageId="23" pageNumber="528" pagination="49 - 58" refId="ref23158" refString="MORSHED S. &amp; PATTON J. L. 2002. - New records of mammals from Iran with systematic comments on hedgehogs (Erinaceidae) and mouse-like hamsters (Calomyscus, Muridae). Zoology in the Middle East 26: 49 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2002.10637921" type="journal article" year="2002">Morshed &amp; Patton 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="KARAMI M. &amp; HUTTERER R. &amp; BENDA P. &amp; SIAHSARVIE R. &amp; KRYSTUFEK B." box="[584,768,670,694]" pageId="23" pageNumber="528" pagination="63 - 102" refId="ref21762" refString="KARAMI M., HUTTERER R., BENDA P., SIAHSARVIE R. &amp; KRYSTUFEK B. 2008. - Annotated check-list of the mammals of Iran. Lynx (Praha) 39 (1): 63 - 102." type="journal article" year="2008">
Karami 
<emphasis box="[664,712,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
; Ziaie 2008). Moreover, it may occur in 
<collectingRegion box="[538,639,696,720]" country="Turkey" name="Gaziantep" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">Gaziantep</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[693,775,696,720]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">Hakkari</collectingRegion>
Provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[263,332,722,746]" name="Turkey" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="KRYSTUFEK B. &amp; VOHRALIK V." box="[348,627,722,747]" pageId="23" pageNumber="528" refId="ref22373" refString="KRYSTUFEK B. &amp; VOHRALIK V. 2009. - Mammals of Turkey and Cyprus. Rodentia II: Cricetinae, Muridae, Spalacidae, Calomyscidae, Capromyidae, Hystricidae, Castoridae. Zalozba Annales, Koper, Slovenia." type="book" year="2009">Kryštufek &amp; Vohralík 2009</bibRefCitation>
) but no specimens are available for confirmation. Hence, actual range has yet to be defined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[132,775,823,1059]" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">
HABITAT. — Relatively little is known about its ecology. It is commonly found in forests at intermediate altitudes under evergreens as well as on barren, dry and rocky mountainsides with little vegetation. It favors mountain steppe regions between 400 and 
<quantity box="[691,770,902,926]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="528" unit="m" value="3500.0">3500 m</quantity>
, and is typically absent from low valleys. Moreover, it favors crevices between stone walls and embankments in small fields and terraced cultivation. In these crevices nests made of woven grass, wool, and other various soft materials have been found (
<bibRefCitation author="LAY D. M." box="[583,677,1008,1033]" pageId="23" pageNumber="528" pagination="1 - 282" refId="ref22594" refString="LAY D. M. 1967. - A study of the mammals of Iran resulting from the street expedition of 1962 - 63. Fieldiana Zoology 54: 1 - 282." type="journal article" year="1967">Lay 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="GRZIMEK B. &amp; KLEIMAN D. G. &amp; GEIST V. &amp; MCDADE M. &amp; TRUMPEY J. E." pageId="23" pageNumber="528" refId="ref20836" refString="GRZIMEK B., KLEIMAN D. G., GEIST V., MCDADE M. C &amp; TRUMPEY J. E. 2004. - Grzimek's Animal Life Encyclopedia. Vol. 16., Detroit, Gale, 670 p." type="book" year="2004">
Grzimek 
<emphasis box="[132,179,1035,1059]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="528">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
